#: ../../../ClangFormatStyleOptions.rst:181
msgid ""
"``InheritParentConfig`` Not a real style, but allows to use the ``.clang-"
"format`` file from the parent directory (or its parent if there is none). If "
"there is no parent file found it falls back to the ``fallback`` style, and "
"applies the changes to that. With this option you can overwrite some parts "
"of your main style for your subdirectories. This is also possible through "
"the command line, e.g.: ``--style={BasedOnStyle: InheritParentConfig, "
"ColumnLimit: 20}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ClangFormatStyleOptions.rst:189
msgid ""
"``InheritParentConfig=<directory-path>`` Same as the above except that the "
"inheritance is redirected to ``<directory-path>``. This is only supported in "
"configuration files."
msgstr ""

